{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11727: When a user specifies a specific key within a v-if directive, Vue should use the user-provided key instead of its internally generated key.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:18.699306+00:00",
  "text": "When a user specifies a specific key within a v-if directive, Vue should use the user-provided key instead of its internally generated key.\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.4.38\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9e045807-4087-46ff-876f-afb0a65a1422)\r\n\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nThe compiled results should be key: 100, key: 2000\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nThe compiled results are actually key: 0, key: 1\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
